trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> objects in a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu"></xref> control.
The SubMenuStyleCollection class is used to store and manage a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> objects in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu> control.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu> control uses the SubMenuStyleCollection class as the underlying data type of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu.LevelSubMenuStyles%2A> property.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu.LevelSubMenuStyles%2A> property provides additional style choices in addition to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu.StaticMenuStyle%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu.DynamicMenuStyle%2A> properties.
The first style in the SubMenuStyleCollection collection corresponds to the submenu style for the first level of the menu.
The second style in the collection corresponds to the submenu style for the second level of the menu, and so on.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Menu.LevelSubMenuStyles%2A> property is most often used to generate a navigation menu, like a Web site map, where menu items at a certain level should have the same appearance, regardless of whether they have submenus.
The SubMenuStyleCollection class inherits most of its members from the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection> class.
For more information on the inherited members, see the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection> collection.
Adds a submenu style to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.OnInsert%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnValidate%2A> methods are called before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> instance is added to the collection, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnInsertComplete%2A> method is called after the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> instance is added.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> instance to add to the collection.
The position in the collection at which the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> instance was inserted.
Determines whether a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection contains a specific <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> instance.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnValidate%2A> method is called to validate the `style` parameter before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection is checked.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> instance to locate in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection.

Copies the contents of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection to an array, starting at a specified array index.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> objects are copied to the destination array in the same order in which the enumerator iterates through the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.

The one-dimensional array that is the destination of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> objects copied from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection.
The `array` must have zero-based indexing.
The zero-based index in `array` at which copying begins.
array is .
index is less than zero.
Creates an <xref:System.Object?displayProperty=fullName> of the data type that corresponds to the specified index.
The CreateKnownType method is a helper function that is used to create an <xref:System.Object> of the data type that corresponds to the specified index.

The index is often determined by using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.GetKnownTypes%2A> method to create an array of supported data types and then searching the array for the desired data type.
The `index` parameter is not used in this implementation of the method and is ignored.
You should always pass in `null` for this parameter.
This implementation of the method always returns an empty <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> object.
> [!NOTE] > This method is used only by control developers.
The index of the data type to create.

Always returns an empty <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object.
Creates an array of <xref:System.Type?displayProperty=fullName> objects that contains the supported data types of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> class.
The GetKnownTypes method is a helper function that is used to create an array of data types supported by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> class.
The array is often searched to determine the index of a desired data type.

The index is then passed to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.CreateKnownType%2A> method to create an <xref:System.Object?displayProperty=fullName> of the corresponding data type.
> [!NOTE] > This method is used only by control developers.
An array of <xref:System.Type?displayProperty=fullName> objects that contains the data types supported by the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> class.
Determines the location of a specified <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnValidate%2A> method is called to validate the `style` parameter before the index is returned.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object to locate in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection.

Inserts a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object into the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection at the specified index.
If index is -1, `style` is inserted at the beginning of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.
If index equals the number of items in the collection, `style` is appended to the end of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnValidate%2A> method is called to validate the style parameter before it is added to the collection.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.OnInsert%2A> method is called before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> object is inserted into the collection, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnInsertComplete%2A> method is called after the object is inserted.

The OnInsert method is called before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.Add%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.Insert%2A> methods.

You can override the OnInsert method in custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> classes to perform custom processing of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> objects before they are added to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnValidate%2A> method is called to validate the style parameter before it is used to locate the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> object to remove from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnRemove%2A> method is called before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> object is removed, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnRemoveComplete%2A> method is called after the object is removed from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.

The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection is read-only.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnRemove%2A> method is called before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle> object is removed from the collection, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.StateManagedCollection.OnRemoveComplete%2A> method is called after the object is removed from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection> collection.
The zero-based index location of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object to remove from the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection is read-only.

Instructs a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyle"></xref> object contained by the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection"></xref> collection to record its entire state to view state.

The SetDirtyObject method is called internally by the <xref:System.Web.UI.IStateManager.SaveViewState%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.Add%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SubMenuStyleCollection.Insert%2A> methods.
